    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-06-17T17:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-06-17T17:45:00-05:00" n="83"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/6–1752:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>.<note n="1" xml:id="d83fn1">Drafted by <persName>Edgar J.
                            Beigel</persName> of the Office of Western European Affairs. Repeated
                        for information to London as telegram 6682 and to Saigon as telegram
                        1984.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-06-17T18:45:00-04:00"
                            >June 17, 1952—6:45 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7404. Pass SRE. <gloss target="#t_Cotel1">Cotel</gloss>. In course <persName
                        corresp="#p_LJ2">Letourneau</persName> talks today,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d83fn2">For an extract from the summary minutes, see <ref
                            target="#d82">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> US side informed Fr that subject appropriations US wld be
                    prepared provide <pb facs="0235" n="203" xml:id="pg_203"/> up to 150 mil dols
                    addl <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1953 aid in support overall Fr effort in
                        <gloss target="#t_IC1">IC</gloss>, which probably will remain, as stated in
                        <persName corresp="#p_LJ2">Letourneau</persName> memo (<gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 7682 June 9),<note n="3" xml:id="d83fn3"
                        >Telegram 7682 from Paris, June 9, not printed, contained a summary of a
                        memorandum received from <persName corresp="#p_LJ2">Letourneau</persName> at
                        Paris on the same day, which provided information on total French
                        expenditures for Indochina in 1952. (601.5151G/6–952)</note> substantially
                    same next year. It might be considered this addl aid wld in effect add to Fr
                    resources to meet increased overall Fr requirements in Eur in 1953. Relation
                    this addl aid to overall US aid to Fr in <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1953
                    and total Fr defense effort in calendar 1953 will be determined in course <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> annual review.</p>
                <p>Fr informed that in view Lisbon understanding, no addl aid available for Fr
                    calendar 1952 budget for <gloss target="#t_IC1">IC</gloss>, but that we are
                    considering <persName corresp="#p_PR1">Pleven</persName> request for add <gloss
                        target="#t_OSP1">OSP</gloss> in 1952.<note n="4" xml:id="d83fn4">For
                        documentation on overall U.S. assistance to France, see <ref
                            target="frus1952-54v06p1">volume <hi rend="smallcaps">vi</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Copies US position paper<note n="5" xml:id="d83fn5">Reference is to document LET
                        D–1/1, “Aid Aspects of <persName corresp="#p_LJ2">Letourneau</persName>
                        Talks,” June 14, not printed. (Conference files, lot 59 D 95, <gloss
                            target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 114)</note> and minutes being pouched marked
                        <persName>Sprouse</persName>. Text communiqué fols in separate tel.<note
                        n="6" xml:id="d83fn6">Regarding the communiqué of June 18, see editorial
                        note, <ref target="#d84">
                            <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
